## Good Commit Examples

These are correct. Each is atomic, clear, and follows the format:

```
docs: create /rules/COMMIT_DISCIPLINE.md
docs: create /rules/CODE_HYGIENE.md
docs: create /docs/TECH_STACK.md
docs: create /docs/RBAC_ROLES_AND_PERMISSIONS.md
feat(db): create src/db/utils/id.ts with generateId using Bun.randomUUIDv7
feat(db): create departments schema table
feat(db): create assets schema table with all required columns
feat(db): create TypeBox schema for assets (insert and select)
feat(api): add GET /api/v1/departments list endpoint
feat(api): add POST /api/v1/departments create endpoint
feat(api): add RBAC permission check middleware
feat(auth): add login endpoint and login page
feat(auth): implement invite-only user registration flow
feat(auth): add accept-invite page with password setup form
feat(auth): implement session timeout (8h max, 2h inactivity)
feat(auth): expire all sessions on user deactivation
feat(ui): add sidebar layout using shadcn-svelte sidebar-08
feat(assets): add asset list page with offset pagination
feat(assets): add asset create form with TypeBox validation
feat(assets): add draft auto-save to asset create form
feat(assets): add QR code display to asset detail page
feat(dashboard): add summary cards (total assets, unverified, etc.)
feat(dashboard): add asset map using Leaflet and OpenStreetMap
fix(api): correct offset calculation in assets pagination
fix(auth): handle expired invite token gracefully with proper error message
chore(deps): install @elysia/openapi and configure Swagger UI at /swagger
chore(deps): pin @sinclair/typebox to version matching elysia
test(api): add tests for POST /api/v1/assets validation and RBAC
ci: add vp check and vp test stages to GitLab pipeline
```

