## Bad Commit Examples

These are wrong. Each violates the rules:

```
# ❌ Too vague — what was fixed? why?
fix: fixed stuff

# ❌ Not imperative mood, not specific
Added some auth features and the login page and also started on assets

# ❌ WIP commits must never be pushed to the main branch
wip

# ❌ Combines multiple unrelated features
feat: implement auth, assets, departments, and dashboard

# ❌ Useless — every commit updates files
update files

# ❌ Wrong mood, no specifics
Adding the database schema

# ❌ Passive voice, too vague
Various bug fixes and improvements

# ❌ Too long and unparseable as a subject line
feat: implement the full authentication flow including login, invite, accept invite page, session management with 8h expiry and 2h inactivity and also deactivation session cleanup and the forgot/reset password pages

# ❌ Temporary / debug code committed
chore: temp console.log to debug auth issue
```

